A steaming ceramic cup of dark coffee sits on a weathered wooden café table, photographed in rich photorealistic detail with dramatic morning light streaming through a rain-speckled window. The coffee's surface shows intricate swirling patterns in the crema. Surrounding the cup are scattered fresh coffee beans and a small vintage brass spoon. In the background, slightly out of focus, sits a red apple and a ripe tomato, creating a subtle visual comparison. The color palette emphasizes warm amber tones contrasting with deep espresso browns. Tiny wisps of steam rise and catch the golden light, creating an almost mystical atmosphere. The composition suggests both comfort and subtle tension, reflecting the dual nature of coffee's reputation. Shot with shallow depth of field, emphasizing the coffee cup as the hero element.
